Color Description
Sapphire cosmetic contact lenses are designed to make your eye color more like the color of the sapphire colored contacts. Being opaque they are more popular with those who have naturally dark coloured eyes because they make the most dramatic change. Brilliant blue colored contact lenses may give a slightly more dramatic effect and the blue colorblends or colors a less dramatic effect.
These soft color lenses are available without vision correction or power. Without power to change eye color only.
Note
Computer pictures only give you an idea of how the sapphire colored contact-lens may look on your eyes because of the influence of your natural eye color and the settings on your computer monitor.
Precaution
  • Washing your hands before handling the contact lens.
  • Not sharing your contact lens with others.
  • Disinfecting the contact lens on a regular basis.
  • Using the proper contact lens solutions.
  • Not wearing the lenses any longer than your doctor has recommended.
  • Don't just top off the storage solution but replace it completely with fresh sterilizing storage solution each time before storing the lenses.Tap water will not do because it isn't sterile or safe.
  • Remember to clean out the lens case at least once a week and leave it air dry before replacing the storage solution.
  • Also it's best to use a brand new lens case every few months especially if your present lens case is starting to look dirty.
